msContents.summary: Collection of letters and documents related to the Council of Trent.

msItem.title: Lettere e scritture passate nel concilio di Trento
Lettere degli signori legati dal concilio...all?ill[ustrissi]mo et r[everendissi]mo card[ina]l Borromeo nel 1562 et 1563, f. 1r
Scrittura data dal amb[asciat]ore di Francia et da Mons. d?Oyssel al re cat[toli]co [Philip II] die prima maii 1563, f. 112r
Scrittura data dal archivesc[o] Granato [Pedro Guerrero] et Braga a? li ssri. legati, f. 125r
Instrutt[ion]e a? Mons. di Vintimiglia [Carlo Visconti] per la corte di Spagna, f. 129r
Proposita et postulata ab oratoribus Christiani regis pro reformatione ecclesiae, f. 135r
Copy of letter without indication of author or addressee, Trento, f. 165r
Articulus primus [-xxxiv], each with responsio legatorum, and responsio cardinalium, f. 171r
Text of 13 proposals with responses, f. 187r
Text of 13 proposals with responses, f. 195r

supportDesc.extent: 212 leaves : 263 x 206 (198 x 115) mm. bound to 266 x 208 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 212; [1-212]; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in cursive script by at least 5 different hands, perhaps at different dates after 1563, in Italy [etc.?]. Item 2 was folded, with address on outside leaf.

binding.p: Contemporary vellum. Upper cover and spine pulling away from text block. Moderate to heavy oxidation of ink on some folios, with perforations of leaves.
